Ya kamata Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take bayarwa don binciken AI
Kai-Fu Lee, wani mai zuba jari da kuma masanin ilimin kere kere da ke aiki a kamfanonin Google, Microsoft da Apple, ya ce, yayin da kasar Sin ke kara aiki a wannan fannin, ya kamata Amurka ta ninka kudaden da take kashewa a binciken kere kere.
Wannan bayanin ya shafi sanarwar da hukumomin gwamnati daban-daban na Amurka suka fitar game da ilimin kere kere, duk da cewa Amurka ba ta da wata dabara ta musamman game da AI.
A shekarar da ta gabata, kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirin da ta yi na zama kasa mafi kirkire-kirkire a fannin kere kere a shekarar 2030.
"Da farko, muna bukatar mu ninka kasafin kudin binciken AI: duk sauran kasashe sun yi nisa da Amurka, kuma muna kokarin kawo wani ci gaba a wannan fannin", in ji Kai-Fu Lee.
A wata hira da ya yi da CNBC a wannan makon, ya kuma ce ninka kudaden zai ninka damar samun wata babbar nasara a fannin fasaha ta wucin gadi a Amurka.
Lee, wanda littafinsa mai suna AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order, wanda Houghton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shi ne shugaban kamfanin Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin kere kere na kasar Sin, wanda ake kira Face++.
A shekarun 1980s, Kai-Fu Lee ya yi aiki a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon a kan tsarin AI wanda ya ci nasara a kan mafi kyawun dan wasan Amurka a lokacin, Othello, sannan ya zama babban jami'in Microsoft Research, kuma ya zama shugaban kamfanin Google na kasar Sin.
Lee ya yaba da nasarar da gwamnatin Amurka ta samu a baya, kamar gasar DARPA, inda aka gudanar da gasar neman zane-zane na mutum-mutumi, kuma ya yi tambaya game da lokacin da za a sake yin gasar, saboda yana ganin hakan zai taimaka wajen gano masu hangen nesa na gaba.
Kai-Fu Lee ya ce, masu bincike a Amirka sukan yi ƙoƙari sosai don su sami tallafin gwamnati.
"Ba kasar Sin ce ke janye mana manyan jami'ai ba, kamfanoni ne", in ji Lee.
A 'yan shekarun nan, Facebook, Google, da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun yi amfani da manyan masana kimiyya don yin aiki a kan ilimin kere kere.
Lee ya ce, sauya manufofin shige da fice zai iya taimaka wa Amurka wajen bunkasa AI.
"Ina ganin cewa ya kamata a ba da katin kore ga masu aikin kere kere da suka samu digirin PhD", in ji shi.
A watan Yulin shekara ta 2017, majalisar dokokin kasar Sin ta fitar da wani shiri na samar da fasahar kere kere ta gaba.
Lee ya lura cewa, National Natural Science Foundation of China tana ba da tallafi ga mambobin jami'o'i a hanyar da ta yi kama da na National Science Foundation na Amurka da sauran kungiyoyin gwamnati da ke ba da tallafi ga masana kimiyya na Amurka, amma ingancin ayyukan ilimi a China ya fi na sauran ƙasashe.
A farkon wannan shekarar, Ma'aikatar Tsaro ta Amurka ta kafa cibiyar hadin gwiwa kan ilimin kere kere, wato Joint Artificial Intelligence Center, wadda za ta hada da masana'antu da masana kimiyya, kuma fadar White House ta sanar da kafa kwamitin da za ta yi nazari kan ilimin kere kere.
A wannan watan, DARPA ta kuma sanar da cewa za ta ba da dala biliyan biyu don wani shiri da ake kira AI Next.
Gidauniyar Kimiyya ta kasa a yanzu tana zuba jari sama da dala biliyan 100 a shekara a binciken AI.
A lokaci guda, shirin Amurka na kafa kwamitin tsaro na fasaha na wucin gadi na kasa ya kasance a kasa a watanni da dama.
